6:
Get a load of these crowds. Bazaars
are really something else.
10: What are they selling over there?
17:
I'm not about to give up this item to
someone who doesn't even know
the first thing about magic. Shoo.
21:
What a strange merchant to chase
off a customer like that...
25:
You guys looking in my direction...
You must be interested in the great
Nellie's magic theory.
36:
Blindly relying on your senses to
weave spells is a thing of the past!
Practical theory is where it's at these
days!
40: Oh? I'd love to hear more.
44:
Haha, that's the attitude I like to see!
Let me make this simple!
47:
For starters... Ta-da! Take a good
look at this ether-detection staff!
48:
It allows us to analyze otherwise
untraceable ether by splitting it into
two disparate elements!
51:
Your average spirit or wizard does
their thing by bending their will to
one of the six elemental forces. Well,
ether detection is the step which
comes right before that.
54:
Grasping the very nature of ether is
something that all high-level
spellcasters must do in their mind.
This staff allows for a more
systematic approach to that!
55:
Meaning theoretically, anyone
should be capable of reaching the
highest echelons of dimensional
sorcery and rewrite reality!
61:
Whoa, give me a sec. I need a
moment to process all that...
64:
Actually, I think you completely lost
me...
70:
What's so hard to understand?! I've
only covered the most basic step so
far!
73:
How about the theoretical model of
simultaneous existence of multiple
crystal sizes in the same space—
88:
*yawn* I'm just drowsy after all that
talking...
90:
One moment... I need a little
pick-me-up!
94:
There, much better! Nothing like a
bit of sugar to revitalize the brain!
104:
Now that my brain's fully functional
again, let's get back on track—
108:
Pretty sure you'd get your point
across faster if we just WATCH you
cast a spell.
113:
Indeed. If you are as knowledgeable
about magic as you claim to be, a
little demonstration should not be
too difficult.
117:
Er, well... How should I put this... You
need a base level of mana before
you can use magic...
121:
Not to mention magic theory isn't a
game of show and tell; I wouldn't be
going to such lengths if it were so
easy to grasp!
130:
Let's just I say I prefer to be careful!
And magic is definitely something to
be cautious with!
134:
Nice way of sugarcoatin' it. Your
smarts are the real deal at least, but
is there any point to this?
139:
You bet there is! Magic theory is a
real thing regardless of whether I
can fling spells or not!
143:
I could even use high-level spells if I
just had mana... Everything matches
up in theory!
147: Hm... I do find this rather fascinating.
150:
No one would make a such a claim
based off a fanciful whim. You must
have done a considerable amount
of research.
155:
Indeed, I have! By the way, I
personally crafted every item you
see here!
163:
Wait... Where have I seen that
pattern before?
168:
You're kidding! I should be the only
person in the world who's ever laid
eyes on this conceptual theory
diagram before today!
172:
I'm sure I saw it at some desert
ruins—oh, don't mind me! We should
get going now.
177:
Wait, I'm not done talking to you!
Where can I find these ruins you
speak of?!
181:
We saw the pattern in the desert
ruins of another world.
190:
Please, you have to take me there! I
must see it for myself!
201: I can't believe such a world exists...
205:
Hope you know that just goin' there's
not gonna turn you into some
almighty sorceress, if that's what
you're hoping for.
211:
We'll see about that, Nimbus! In a
different world, there's a good
chance the elements and ether
behave in a completely different
manner!
215:
There's so many things I'll have to try
out!
218:
I'd better make sure to have lots of
sweets on hand!
